# Security Environment Variables for Production

# Required for production - Add these to your Vercel environment variables

## Database Security
DATABASE_URL="your_postgresql_connection_string"

## Authentication & Encryption
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your_super_secret_jwt_key_at_least_32_characters_long"
NEXTAUTH_URL="https://yourdomain.vercel.app"
ENCRYPTION_SECRET="your_encryption_key_for_sensitive_data_at_least_32_chars"

## Rate Limiting (Redis) - Highly Recommended for Production
# Sign up for Upstash Redis (free tier available)
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL="https://your-redis-instance.upstash.io"
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN="your_redis_token"

## CORS Security
ALLOWED_ORIGINS="https://yourdomain.vercel.app,https://your-custom-domain.com"

## SMS Service
VOODOO_API_KEY="your_voodoo_sms_api_key"

## Optional API Protection
API_KEY="your_api_key_for_external_access"

# Environment Configuration
NODE_ENV="production"

## Security Notes:
# 1. NEXTAUTH_SECRET: Generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`
# 2. ENCRYPTION_SECRET: Generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`
# 3. Never commit these values to Git
# 4. Use different secrets for staging/production
# 5. Rotate secrets regularly (every 90 days recommended)
# 6. Enable Vercel's environment variable encryption
# 7. Set up Redis for proper rate limiting in production